node.text:
Day 11 of Tokyo 2020 did not hold back being an incredibly emotional one! What an unforgettable day! 🤩

Podiums swept, legends created and world records broken! 🔥

A Historic first Para Badminton Gold for Malaysia, back-to-back Sitting Volleyball titles for Iran and soccer ball Brazil win the battle of the South American Football 5-A-Side giants! 

Watch Day 11 Overall Highlights | Tokyo 2020

node.text:
Joy in the rain!🥇 ⁣
⁣
Lisbeli Vera Andrade (@lisbelyvera ) 🇻🇪 had the perfect answer to the school bullies who used to make her life a misery at school in Venezuela because she was born without part of her left arm.⁣ 

Lisbeli won 100m and 200m T47 gold at #Tokyo2020. 🥇 🥇 
⁣
“When I crossed the finish line I didn't realise I'd won and I didn’t know how to express my feelings in the moment. I trusted myself to win the race.”⁣
⁣
“When I was at school I was teased because I was missing that part of my body, and that always made me feel different. I would lock myself in my house and say I didn't want to go out.⁣
⁣
“Those jokes made me mature because I knew that at some point I was going to have to face life, that I wasn't always going to be protected and that I had to stand up for myself."⁣
⁣
More on this via our Stories. 
⁣
(Descriptions: It is night, and raining. Lisbeli jumps up on the track, celebrating wildly. Her hair is long and mid-jump it swooshes into the sky. Third picture is Brittani Mason side by side racing with Lisbeli. The final shot is Lisbeli taking in the moment.)⁣
⁣
#Paralympics #Tokyo2020 #ParaAthletics #Venezuela ⁣
⁣
📸: James Varghese Photography.
